About Anya Zenooz

When we listen,
we see ourselves

Anya Zenooz is a first-time filmmaker and sophomore at La Jolla Country Day School in San Diego, CA. She founded the Mirror Project, a global initiative examining how young people experience stereotypes, and directed the companion documentary Reflections. Her work explores how social narratives and digital media shape young adult identity and decision-making. She is active in Model UN and Mock Trial and serves as co-captain of her school's dance team.

Questions

FAQ

What is the Mirror Project? +
The Mirror Project is a global youth cultural exchange built around video interviews. We travel the world to capture the voices of young people and share them globally.
How can I be interviewed? +
Head to our "Share With Us" page and fill out the interest form. Our team reviews submissions and reaches out when filming in your region.
Is this free to participate in? +
Yes, completely. The Mirror Project is nonprofit-minded. Participating, watching, and sharing are all free.
How can I support the project? +
Share our videos, submit your story, and spread the word. For sponsorship or partnership, reach out via email.
How many countries have you filmed in? +
We've filmed across all 6 continents and in dozens of countries. Our goal is to represent every major region and culture on Earth.
